<div class="container py-5" data-aos="fade-up">
  <nav aria-label="breadcrumb" class="mb-4">
    <ol class="breadcrumb">
      <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/" class="text-primary text-decoration-none">Home</a></li>
      <li class="breadcrumb-item active" aria-current="page">Privacy Policy</li>
    </ol>
  </nav>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-8">
      <h1 class="display-4 fw-extrabold mb-3">Privacy <span class="text-primary">Policy</span></h1>
      <p class="text-muted fs-5 mb-5">Your privacy is our priority. Read how we protect, store, and utilize your personal information.</p>

      <div class="mb-5">
        <h3 class="fw-bold mb-3"><i class="bi bi-shield-lock text-primary me-2"></i> 1. Information Collection</h3>
        <p class="text-muted lh-lg">
          At ToyBerry, we collect only the necessary information to complete your orders and provide a personalized experience. This includes:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-muted lh-lg">
          <li><strong>Personal details:</strong> Recipient name, shipping address, contact phone number, and email.</li>
          <li><strong>Payment credentials:</strong> Encrypted transaction reference IDs (we do not store raw card numbers; online transactions are securely routed through certified platforms like Stripe).</li>
          <li><strong>Browsing patterns:</strong> Dynamic search histories, page views, and items added to wishlists.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-5">
        <h3 class="fw-bold mb-3"><i class="bi bi-eye text-primary me-2"></i> 2. Use of Information</h3>
        <p class="text-muted lh-lg">
          We use your data strictly to fulfill orders, issue invoices, coordinate shipping partners, process refund claims, and send optional promotional newsletters (which you can unsubscribe from at any time). We will never sell, trade, or leak your private details to marketing brokers.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-5">
        <h3 class="fw-bold mb-3"><i class="bi bi-cookie text-primary me-2"></i> 3. Cookies and Analytics</h3>
        <p class="text-muted lh-lg">
          ToyBerry uses secure browser cookies to store items in your cart, persist your session state, and monitor website speeds. We integrate Google Analytics to analyze platform traffic trends and verify compatibility across mobile devices.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-5">
        <h3 class="fw-bold mb-3"><i class="bi bi-database-check text-primary me-2"></i> 4. Data Retention & Deletion</h3>
        <p class="text-muted lh-lg">
          We retain your shipping details in our encrypted database as required by Indian taxation laws for order reporting. If you would like us to permanently delete your guest information or profile account, please send a request to our data protection officer.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Right Sidebar Info Card -->
    <div class="col-lg-4">
      <div class="card border-0 bg-light rounded-4 p-4 mt-lg-5 shadow-sm">
        <h5 class="fw-bold mb-4">Privacy Concerns?</h5>
        <p class="text-muted small">Our Data Protection Officer (DPO) is dedicated to managing customer confidentiality and processing account deletions.</p>
        
        <hr class="my-3 text-muted">
        
        <div class="d-flex align-items-center gap-3 mb-3">
          <div class="bg-white p-2 rounded-3 text-primary shadow-sm"><i class="bi bi-envelope fs-5"></i></div>
          <div>
            <div class="small text-muted">Privacy Officer</div>
            <div class="fw-bold" style="font-size: 0.95rem;">privacy@toyberry.in</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary-custom w-100 rounded-pill mt-3 py-2 fw-bold text-center">Contact DPO</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
